    invp:description """
The Kijun-sen, or base line, is an indicator and important component of the<a data-component="link" data-ordinal="1" data-source="inlineLink" data-type="internalLink" href="https://www.investopedia.com/terms/i/ichimokuchart.asp"> Ichimoku Kinko Hyo</a> method of technical analysis, which is also known as the Ichimoku cloud.

The Kijun-sen is the midpoint price of the last 26-periods, and therefore an indicator of short- to medium-term price <a data-component="link" data-ordinal="1" data-source="inlineLink" data-type="internalLink" href="https://www.investopedia.com/terms/m/momentum.asp">momentum</a>. The indicator aids in assessing the trend, and can also be useful for identifying trading opportunities when combined with the other components of the Ichimoku cloud.

